eans: I want precise cycles, and I want the VM too<br /><br />   This would result in EOPNOTSUPP for the case we know is buggy (but<br />presumably work on some other CPUs that don't have the problem)<br /><br /> - "cycles:pp" is "I want precise cycles, and I don't care about virtualization"<br /><br />   This would do whatever works. So it would basically become<br />host-only, but if you don't want precise cycles (so no ":pp") then<br />whatever our old behavior was (presumably "profile the virtual machine<br />too") would be what happens.<br /><br />That sounds like (a) the interface that people want and (b) entirely<br />backwards-compatible for all cases that can matter (where "oops, I<br />crashed the VM" case does not matter).<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
